Definition: a rare genetic condition characterized by an eruption of exposed skin occurring in childhood and photosensitivity with severe sunburn
Example: inherited as a recessive autosomal trait in which DNA repair processes are defective so they are more likely to chromosome breaks and cancers when exposed to ultraviolet light
Synonyms: xeroderma, a, rare, genetic, condition, characterized, by, an, eruption, of, exposed, skin, occurring, in, childhood, and, photosensitivity, with, severe, sunburn, inherited, as, recessive, autosomal, trait, which, DNA, repair, processes, are, defective, so, they, more, likely, to, chromosome, breaks, cancers, when, ultraviolet, light
Category: noun.state
